box": [805.1, 711.7, 814.4, 732.5]}, {"text": "232.6", "bbox": [831.6, 711.7, 892.5, 734.6]}, {"text": "22%", "bbox": [953.6, 711.7, 995.0, 734.6]}, {"text": "$ 204.3", "bbox": [1022.3, 711.7, 1097.3, 734.6]}, {"text": "23%", "bbox": [1159.9, 713.0, 1195.7, 732.2]}, {"text": "Total Revenue", "bbox": [75.0, 763.8, 186.8, 784.0]}, {"text": "Total revenue increased by 34% and 20% during the years ended December 31, 2010 and 2009, respectively. Total revenue increased to $1,413.0 million", "bbox": [118.8, 794.1, 1186.3, 813.5]}, {"text": "during the year ended December 31, 2010 from $1,052.2 million during the year ended December 31, 2009 from $874.9 million during the year ended", "bbox": [75.0, 815.8, 1132.4, 835.5]}, {"text": "December 31, 2008. Total revenue growth was driven by the continued adoption of da Vinci surgery. We believe that robotic surgery will be adopted surgical", "bbox": [75.0, 837.4, 1174.1, 857.4]}, {"text": "procedure by surgical procedure, driving higher system and recurring revenue. Our revenue growth during the periods presented reflects penetration in our", "bbox": [75.0, 859.8, 1151.3, 879.2]}, {"text": "target procedures. dVH and dVP are our two largest procedures, representing more than 70% of our total procedures over the past several years.", "bbox": [75.0, 881.7, 1074.7, 901.1]}, {"text": "Revenue within the United States accounted for 80%, 79%, and 78% of total revenue during the years ended December 31, 2010, 2009, and 2008,", "bbox": [118.8, 919.0, 1145.2, 938.6]}, {"text": "respectively. We believe domestic revenue has accounted for the large majority of total revenue primarily due to the ability of patients to choose their provider", "bbox": [75.0, 941.2, 1166.5, 960.4]}, {"text": "and method of treatment in the U.S.", "bbox": [75.0, 962.8, 326.2, 982.4]}, {"text": "45", "bbox": [625.3, 999.4, 643.9, 1020.2]}]}